1: Run CleanText.py, it will use train.csv and output CleanText_out.csv
2: Run RemoveInfrequentWords.py, it will use CleanText_out.csv and output RemoveInfrequentWords_out.csv
3: Run sparceARFFGen.py, it will use RemoveInfrequentWords_out.csv and the output can be redirected to an ARFF file (sparceARFFGen_out.arff in this example)
4: Using Weka, select the top k attributes using some criteria

The data can now be used to build the model.
